      "writtenOn": "2026-07-17T13:25:36Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "In this patch, I have just implemented D-Bus object for each of the component state sensor, responsible to measure a single state set exposed for a state sensor defined in PLDM.\n\nThe D-Bus interface and its corresponding property has not yet implemented, and is planned to be done in the next few commits in the relation chain. \n\nThe reason is that:\n1. Implementing component state sensor in this patch is making the patch larger.\n2. Also, according to our design, we will have to define appropriate PDI for each of the implementing state set. However, we haven\u0027t submitted the corresponding PDI yet. Thus, I have decided to postponed that implementation.\n\nRegarding the mapping relation of availability and operational status, I agreed that we should make some agreement and have submitted a design docs stating these mapping relation. Let\u0027s discuss this problem there.\n\nhttps://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/docs/+/92069",
